repos.name: assemble-contrib-anchors
repos.description: Assemble plugin for creating anchor tags from generated html.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-anchors-example
repos.description: Usage examples for assemble-contrib-anchors, an Assemble plugin for generating adding anchors to headings.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-contextual
repos.description: Generates a JSON file containing the context of each page. Basic plugin to help see what's happening in the build.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-lunr
repos.description: Assemble plugin for creating a search engine within your static site using lunr.js.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-lunr-examples
repos.description: Usages examples for assemble-contrib-lunr, a search plugin for Assemble.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-markdown
repos.description: Convert markdown files to HTML using marked.js. This plugin is an alternative to Assemble's markdown Handlebars helpers. Both are useful in different scenarios.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-permalinks
repos.description: Permalinks plugin for Assemble, the static site generator for Grunt.js and Yeoman. This plugin enables powerful and configurable URI replacement patterns, presets, uses Moment.js for parsing dates, and much more.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-toc
repos.description: Create a table of contents in the generated HTML, using Cheerio.js

repos.name: assemble-contrib-toc-example
repos.description: Example for generating a Table of Contents using Assemble.

repos.name: assemble-contrib-wordcount
repos.description: Assemble plugin for displaying a word-count on blog posts or pages.

repos.name: boilerplate-bootstrap
repos.description: Build Bootstrap with Assemble instead of Jekyll.

repos.name: boilerplate-gist-blog
repos.description: Use Assemble to create a blog from GitHub Gists.

repos.name: boilerplate-markdown
repos.description: Use Assemble to generate HTML pages from markdown content. Useful for wikis, gh-pages, documentation and blogs or sites with markdown posts.

repos.name: boilerplate-site
repos.description: Demonstrates how to use Assemble to build a site. Includes layouts, pages, partials, and markdown content.

repos.name: boilerplate-swig
repos.description: Example of using swig templates with Assemble.

repos.name: boilerplates
repos.description: Boilerplates for Assemble. Each boilerplate offers something different: static site generation, h5bp, Bootstrap, swig, markdown, blog generation, etc.
